==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Triungulus
<hw>Tri*un"gu*lus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Triunguli</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Tri-</er>, and <er>Ungulate</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
active young larva of any oil beetle. It has feet armed with three
claws, and is parasitic on bees. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <cref>Oil
beetle</cref>, under <er>Oil</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Triunity</ent>⟦br⟧
